casebody.data:
Sarah Ruth McFadden SCOTT, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11208. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 12, 1945. Henry Clay Agnew, of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. J. Charles Dennis, U. S. Atty., of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and IIEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Good cause therefor appearing, ordered that motion of appellant to dismiss her appeal be, and hereby is granted, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
